author: Russell Brand
description:
In this deep-dive, I break down the latest twist in the Epstein saga: Congress has voted to force the release of the Epstein files, Trump has signed it, and now the establishment is scrambling. From national-security carveouts to sudden “ongoing investigations,” you can already see the machinery of power moving to limit what the public gets to see — and what they don’t. We look at why this moment matters, what the political class is trying to shield, and how the fight over transparency reveals far more than the files themselves.
